                     <decoNote ana="#xx">
                        <ab>Deeply engraved, red painted square frame</ab>
                        <locus>Around inscription</locus>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote>
                        <ab>Three plain crosses: the central bears linear serifs, is incised and
                           heavily painted in red; the right is only painted, as would have probably
                           also been the left one, now totally faded. </ab>
                        <locus>Below the lower frame line</locus>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote>
                        <ab>Linear cross flanked by a pair of heraldically depicted birds, whose red
                           color is partially faded </ab>
                        <locus>In a square attached to the upper frame</locus>
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote>
                        <ab>Zigzag-like pattern in red paint</ab>
                        <locus>Alongside the the left vertical frame. A similar motif may have
                           originally existed on the right side as well. </locus>
